deck: Main antagonist of the 'Hatchet' movie series, this towering undead monstrosity haunts the swamps around New Orleans, killing anyone who ventures too close to his home.
description:
Born a deformed child from a secret affair in the Bayou, Victor's father (Thomas) tried to keep his son a secret... both from the outside world and his then dying wife. Mostly to protect the boy from the neighborhood children who taunt and harass his son... but also to hide his betrayal of his dead wife from his friends and family.

One Halloween night, some local kids decided to scare Victor by throwing firecrackers into his house. This in turn led to the home catching fire and trapping the young Crowley inside behind a locked door. In a panic, Thomas frantically tried to free his son. Picking up a hatchet, the elder Crowley tried to chop his way through the front door to save his boy. Unbeknownst to Thomas, Victor was pressed up on the other side, still trying to free himself and keep away from the fire. Sadly, Thomas accidentally kills his son with the hatchet.

Despite dying, Victor somehow came back... and has been stalking the Bayou ever since... killing those who get too close to his house.

Has starred in three movies, each installment revealing new information involving his past and various characters' connection to it. He has also crossed paths with comic duo Hack/Slash.
name: Victor Crowley

deck: Left on a small town orphanage's doorstep, Huck was raised and cared for in the orphanage he was dropped off. Quiet, a slow learner, yet humble and gentle, Huck uses his special abilities to do a good deed everyday. In return, the people he has helped keeps his abilities a secret.
description:
Origin

Very little is known so far of Huck's true beginning, but his earliest known moment dates back when two ladies from the orphanage discovered him at their doorstep, with a note that simply says "Please Love Him." From that day onward, the orphanage raised him and thought him to do a good deed everyday.

Prelude

Huck pounced from car to car and ran all the way to a seashore cliff, presumably for days without stopping, and dived down into the bottom of the ocean to find a golden chain that belongs to a newcomer in his town, Diane, a young woman with red hair. He leaves the golden chain at her doorstep, rings her doorbell, and spectates her in a distance, while expressing a smile for a job well done.

The next morning Diane was invited to Ms. Taylor's house for coffee. Ms. Taylor is an elder who is a local of the town. She explains to the young woman about Huck. She fills her in with what she knows about how the town received him and his motives in doing the right thing. Of course, Diane did not seem to believe what she just heard at first. Ms. Taylor tells Diane that the town has been blessed with a secret, and it is crucial that it remains a secret.

On Monday, Huck helped out a neighbor clear space for his new barn.

On Tuesday, he woke up early in the morning to throw the entire town's trash out.

On Wednesday, he obstructed a bunch of cars behind him at a Drive-Thru just to buy the food for them with his own money instead.

On Thursday, in the middle of the night, Diane comes across Huck while driving her car. She noticed that he was missing his shoes and was soaking wet.

On Friday, in the morning, Diane explains to Ms. Taylor what she just saw last night. Ms. Taylor shows her the newspaper headline, titled "Missing Fishermen Safe and Well." It was Huck who found the fishermen last night, that is why he was wet at that time. Diane questioned Huck's motives. He can make himself wealthy if he wanted to, but why does he still work as a gas station attendant in a small town and lives in a small house? Ms. Taylor says that some things in life hold more value than riches, that maybe Huck just wants to make people happy.

As Huck decided what to do next, he overheard the T.V. in front of him, stating that over 200 Northern African schoolgirls have been kidnapped. Huck latched on to a plane to track the girls down. A handful of gunmen has the young girls as hostages, already planning to move out of their current location. While one of the gunmen is interacting with the children, Huck dive-bombs to the other gunmen, knocking them out and causing a shock wave, but not as strong though. As the last gunman saw Huck, he was terrified to do anything. Huck took the gunman's rifle and broke it into two, while saying to take off his glasses. The gunman was still terrified, so Huck takes the glasses off himself and gently flung him to the other gunmen's unconscious bodies. Huck pulls out a bag full of candy to give to the children to lighten up the mood and asked them to do him a favor and not tell anyone he was the one who rescued them.

The news about the schoolgirls, safely coming out of the Sambisa Forest (where the gunmen held the children hostage), unharmed, happy and eating candy, but refusing to tell the one who saved them, has been broadcasted to television later that evening. Diane was watching the news with, presumably a friend, and told him that the person who saved the children was Huck.

On Saturday, in the morning, as Huck wakes up to feed his dog, named Mickey, he looks at the window, and is shocked to see the media and press swarming his house.

Diane is in her house, watching the news. A boy approaches him for his violin session with her, but she makes the boy fall asleep. Diane is also special like Huck...

Meanwhile, Huck feels upset. The local seniors and Ms. Taylor comes to his house and tries to comfort him. The seniors know that Diane told the media everything about Huck, and they were furious at her. Ms. Taylor suggested on moving Huck to another place until the media loses track of Huck. As Huck takes a glance at the television, he sees a woman who is upset as well, and he presumes that she came for help.

Huck, without looking back, steps out of his house, even though the seniors tried to stop him. The press swarms all over him, but his first priority is to help the lady in the television. He approaches the lady asking for help, but not without saying "excuse me" to those who were blocking his way. The lady tells Huck to find her husband (who has been missing for half a decade), even if he is dead or alive just to give her closure.

Then a middle-aged couple approaches Huck asking him to find their daughter, who has been missing for eighteen months.

A young woman asks Huck to find her brother, who was kidnapped in Afghanistan.

Finally, a boy asks him to find his missing dog.

Huck writes all of this down to keep track and leaves to do his thing. As he leaves, Diane watches him in her house, shedding a tear, presumably feeling guilty of what she has done.

He looks for the missing husband first. The people follow him and a news chopper records him.

Then he finds the missing brother about to be killed in a truck, but Huck saves him by tumbling the vehicle, knocking out the hostile men and catching the man in a flash.

Meanwhile, a scientist known as Professor Orlov observes Huck in his lab and in a bar in North Carolina, a bearded man smiles in joy as he watches the television. Someone asks him why he is smiling, and the bearded man says that he has finally seen his brother, who he has been searching for his entire life...
name: Huck

deck: A young man who became the new Falcon after being experimented on by Doctor Mallus. After being imbued with Redwings DNA, Joaquin was unable to change back due to his new healing factor, courtesy of Redwings vampiric nature.
description:
Origin

Joaquin Torres is seventeen years old living somewhere between Tuscon, AZ and Sonoita, AZ. He came to America from Mexico illegally with his mother and grandmother when he was a young boy. Joaquin is a Samaritan, one who runs food, water, and medicine to broder crossers so they don't starve or die before they reach their destination.

On a border run delivering water, Joaquin was abducted by the Sons of the Serpent and delivered to a lab in New York operated by Dr. Karl Malus. When Joaquin's grandmother, Mariana, made a request to Captain America on the news to look into his disappearance, Sam Wilson investigated and was captured himself. Malus experimented on them both. Sam's transformation into Cap Wolf was temporary. However, splicing Redwing's DNA irreversibly onto the younger man's, Joaquin was permanently changed into a falcon/human hybrid complete with arm wings, falcon eyes, and telepathic connection to Redwing. Also, due to Redwing's vampiric nature from his run-in with Baron Blood, Joaquin's regenerative abilities prevent his transformation from being reversed.

While recovering in the hospital from Malus' experimentation, Misty Knight and Dennis Dunphy took turns watching over him. Joaquin proved to be a bit of a handful on a couple of occasions, having taken to flying around the hospital whenever he became bored. As Sam Wilson continued his investigation into Malus and the Sons of the Serpent, he came into conflict with Viper and Serpent Solutions. Discovering he and Redwing shared a telepathic link with Sam, Joaquin sensed Sam in danger and flew out a hospital window and arrived in time to catch Sam in mid-fall after he had been pushed out a window. With Sam paralyzed by Asp, Joaquin had to fight off Serpent Solutions by himself until he received help from Diamondback, Misty Knight, and Demolition Man. After Viper and his group had been defeated, Joaquin designed his own costume and declared himself the new Falcon.
name: Falcon (Torres)
